SIMPLE: imponderable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imponderable
<hw>Im*pon"der*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>ponderable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>impond⟦eacute⟧rable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not ponderable; without
sensible or appreciable weight; incapable of being weighed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imponderable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Imponderable
<hw>Im*pon"der*a*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An
imponderable substance or body; specifically, in the plural, a name
formerly applied to heat, light, electricity, and magnetism, regarded as
subtile fluids destitute of weight but in modern science little
used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imponderableness</ent>⟦br⟧
